==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tumbledung
<hw>Tum"ble*dung`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous species of scaraboid beetles belonging to
<gen>Scarabaeus</gen>, <gen>Copris</gen>, <gen>Phanaeus</gen>, and
allied genera. The female lays her eggs in a globular mass of dung which
she rolls by means of her hind legs to a burrow excavated in the earth
in which she buries it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tumbler</ent>⟦br⟧
